Krub ExtraLight Regular (Krub-ExtraLight.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Krub' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight' = NID 1 'Krub ExtraLight'.

Mac NID 6

NID 6 is 'Krub-ExtraLightItalic', Everything looks good.

Krub ExtraLight Italic (Krub-ExtraLightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Krub' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight Italic' = NID 1 'Krub ExtraLight' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Krub Light Regular (Krub-Light.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Krub' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light' = NID 1 'Krub Light'.

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Krub' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light Italic' = NID 1 'Krub Light' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Krub Regular (Krub-Regular.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Krub-Regular', Everything looks good.

Pass

Krub Medium Regular (Krub-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Krub' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'Krub Medium'.

Pass

Krub Medium Italic (Krub-MediumItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Krub' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium Italic' = NID 1 'Krub Medium' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Unless you have entered into a specific license agreement granting you additional rights, your use of this software is limited by the terms of the actual license agreement you have entered into with Monotype. Krub SemiBold Regular (Krub-SemiBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Krub' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold' = NID 1 'Krub SemiBold'.

Pass

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '

NID 6 is 'Krub-SemiBoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Krub SemiBold Italic (Krub-SemiBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Krub-SemiBoldItalic', Everything looks good.

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Krub' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold Italic' = NID 1 'Krub SemiBold' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Krub-BoldItalic', Everything looks good.
